def plot_garbage(loader, s, size = 5):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(size, size, figsize=(10,10))
    indexes = np.random.randint(low=0, high=len(loader.dataset), size=size*size)
    fig.suptitle(s)
    for i in range(size):
        for j in range(size):
            idx = indexes[i * size + j]

            image, label = loader.dataset[idx]
            image = image.permute(1, 2, 0)
            image = image * torch.tensor([0.5, 0.5, 0.5]) + torch.tensor([0.5, 0.5, 0.5])
            image = image.clip(0, 1)

            axs[i, j].imshow(image)
            axs[i, j].axis('off')
            axs[i, j].set_title(f"{loader.dataset.dataset.classes[label]}")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

In [11]:



     


num_classes = len(dataset.classes)
loss_function = nn.CrossEntropyLoss().to(device)

def train(model, optimizer, train_loader):
    model.train()
    loss_list = []
    accuracy_list = []

    time_one = time.time()
    for images, labels in train_loader:
        images = images.to(device)
        labels = labels.to(device)

        outputs = model.forward(images)
        loss = loss_function(outputs, labels)

        optimizer.zero_grad()
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        loss_list.append(loss)
        accuracy_list.append(torch.mean(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1) == labels, dtype = float))

    diff_time = time.time() - time_one
    return loss_list, accuracy_list, diff_time

def validation(model, validation_loader):
    model.eval()
    f1_score_list = []
    loss_list = []
    accuracy_list = []

    time_one = time.time()
    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in validation_loader:
            images = images.to(device)
            labels = labels.to(device)

            outputs = model.forward(images)
            loss = loss_function(outputs, labels)

            f1_score_list.append(torch.tensor(f1_score(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1).cpu(), labels.cpu(), average = 'macro')))
            loss_list.append(loss)
            accuracy_list.append(torch.mean(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1) == labels, dtype = float))

    diff_time = time.time() - time_one
    return f1_score_list, loss_list, accuracy_list, diff_time

def test(model, test_loader):
    f1_score_list = []

    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in test_loader:
            images = images.to(device)
            labels = labels.to(device)

            outputs = model.forward(images)

            f1_score_list.append(torch.tensor(f1_score(torch.argmax(outputs, dim = 1).cpu(), labels.cpu(), average = 'macro')))
    return f1_score_list



     















In [12]:



     


def experiment(model):
    f1_valid_for_graph = []
    optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr = learning_rate)

    for epoch in range(epochs):
        print(f"Epoch: {epoch + 1}/{epochs} ")
        train_loss, accuracy_train, time_train = train(model, optimizer, train_loader)

        print(f"train loss = {torch.stack(train_loss).mean():.3f}, "
              f"train accuracy = {torch.stack(accuracy_train).mean():.3f}, "
              f"train time = {time_train:.2f} "
        )

        f1_score_list, validation_loss, accuracy_validation, time_validation = validation(model, validation_loader)

        print(f"validation loss = {torch.stack(validation_loss).mean():.3f}, "
              f"validation accuracy = {torch.stack(accuracy_validation).mean():.3f}, "
              f"validation time = {time_validation:.2f}, "
              f"f1-score = {torch.stack(f1_score_list).mean():.3f} \n"
        )

        f1_valid_for_graph.append(torch.stack(f1_score_list).mean())

    f1_score_test = test(model, test_loader)
    print(f"Test f1-score:{torch.stack(f1_score_test).mean():.3f} ")
    return f1_valid_for_graph, torch.stack(f1_score_test).mean()



     















In [13]:



     


def plot_f1_score(f1, epochs, name):
    plt.plot(range(epochs), f1, marker="o", color="darkblue")
    plt.title(f"{name}")
    plt.xlabel("Epoch")
    plt.xticks([i for i in range(epochs)])
    plt.ylabel("f1-score")
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

In [14]:



     


def vgg16_random_weights(num_classes):
    #     
    model = models.vgg16(weights=None)  #    
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = True  #   
    model.classifier[6] = nn.Linear(model.classifier[6].in_features, num_classes)
    return model


def vgg16_transfer(num_classes):
    model = models.vgg16(weights=models.VGG16_Weights.DEFAULT)

    #  features ( ),  
    for param in model.features.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    model.avgpool = nn.Sequential(
        nn.Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=3, padding=1),
        nn.BatchNorm2d(256),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=3, padding=1),
        nn.BatchNorm2d(128),
        nn.ReLU(),
        nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((5, 5))
    )

    model.classifier = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(128 * 5 * 5, 1024),
                                     nn.ReLU(),
                                     nn.Dropout(0.3),
                                     nn.Linear(1024, num_classes)
    )

    return model

GoogLeNet¶










In [19]:



     


def googlenet_random_weights(num_classes):
    model = models.googlenet(weights=None, init_weights=True, aux_logits=False)  #  aux_logits=False
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = True  #   

    #   
    model.fc = nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, num_classes)
    return model

def googlenet_transfer(num_classes):
    model = models.googlenet(weights=models.GoogLeNet_Weights.DEFAULT)

    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    model.fc = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(1024, 512),
                             nn.ReLU(),
                             nn.Linear(512, num_classes)
    )

    return model

def resnet34_random_weights(num_classes):
    model = models.resnet34(weights=None)
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = True  #   

    #    
    model.fc = nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, num_classes)
    return model

def resnet34_transfer(num_classes):
    model = models.resnet34(weights=models.ResNet34_Weights.DEFAULT)
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    model.fc = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(512, 256),
                             nn.ReLU(),
                             nn.Linear(256, num_classes)
    )

    return model

In [29]:



     


def resnet50_random_weights(num_classes):
    model = models.resnet50(weights=None)
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = True  #   

    #    
    model.fc = nn.Linear(model.fc.in_features, num_classes)
    return model

def resnet50_transfer(num_classes):
    model = models.resnet50(weights=models.ResNet50_Weights.DEFAULT)
    for param in model.parameters():
        param.requires_grad = False

    model.fc = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(2048, 512),
                             nn.ReLU(),
                             nn.Dropout(0.5),
                             nn.Linear(512, num_classes)
    )

    return model

name_models = [
    'VGG-16 random',
    'VGG-16 transfer',
    'GoogLeNet random',
    'GoogLeNet transfer',
    'ResNet-34 random',
    'ResNet-34 transfer',
    'ResNet-50 random',
    'ResNet-50 transfer'
]

f1_test = [
    f1_test_vgg16_random,
    f1_test_vgg16_transfer,
    f1_test_googlenet_random,
    f1_test_googlenet_transfer,
    f1_test_resnet34_random,
    f1_test_resnet34_transfer,
    f1_test_resnet50_random,
    f1_test_resnet50_transfer
]

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
bars = plt.bar(name_models, f1_test, color = 'darkblue', edgecolor = 'black')
plt.xlabel(" ( )", fontsize = 14)
plt.ylabel(" F1", fontsize = 14)

for bar in bars:
    yval = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, yval + 0.01, round(yval, 2), ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=12)

plt.title(" F1   ", fontsize=16)
plt.xticks(rotation = 45, ha = 'right')
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.show()
